**[lint-style]** reported by [reviewdog](https://github.com/reviewdog/reviewdog) :dog:
```suggestion [_root_.Finite ] (h : Basis R M) : Module.Finite R M := by ```

No need to split cases here
```suggestion
  simp_rw [Algebra.norm_apply,  LinearMap.det_conj _ e.toLinearEquiv]; congr; ext; simp
```
The same proof doesn't work for the trace version, because `trace_conj'` has a `Module.free` assumption (which should be removable like `det_conj`).

This could be used to golf [Algebra.discr_eq_discr_of_algEquiv](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/RingTheory/Discriminant.html#Algebra.discr_eq_discr_of_algEquiv) and remove unnecessary assumptions.
This became longer because the statement is more general?
Yes. We removed the finite-free assumption.
